comment: * Writes an EventLog event capturing the performance of system config file writes. * The event log entry is formatted like this: * 525000 commit_sys_config_file (name|3),(time|2|3), where name is * a short unique name representing the type of configuration file and time is * duration in the {@link SystemClock#uptimeMillis()} time base. * * @hide

methods.name: public void setStartTime(@UptimeMillisLong long startTime)
methods.comment:
* Override the start timestamp.  Use this method when it's desired to include the time
     * taken by the preparation of the configuration data in the overall duration of the
     * "commitSysConfigFile" event.
     *
     * @param startTime Overridden start time, in system uptime milliseconds

methods.name: public void onStartWrite()

* Invoked just before the configuration file writing begins.
